                     String sourceFile,
                     Fort ontology,
                     Fort quotedIsa)
                       throws CycConnectionException,
                              CycApiException
        Deprecated. 
        Imports an OWL ontology.
        Parameters:
        uri - the URI of the ontology
        prefix - the prefix to append to names of new constants created for terms in the ontology
        sourceFile - the path for the file from which to import the ontology, if not from the URI
        ontology - the existing FortImpl representing the ontology, if we are to update an already-imported ontology
        quotedIsa - the collection of which newly created terms should be quoted instances. If null, Cyc will create one.
        Returns:
        the FortImpl representing the imported ontology
        Throws:
        CycConnectionException - if a communications error occurs
        CycApiException - if the Cyc server returns an error

      • importOwlOntology

        public Fort importOwlOntology(String uri,
                     String prefix,
                     String sourceFile,
                     Fort ontology,
                     Fort quotedIsa,
                     Fort cyclist)
                       throws CycConnectionException,
                              CycApiException
        Deprecated. 
        Imports an OWL ontology.
        Parameters:
        uri - the URI of the ontology
        prefix - the prefix to append to names of new constants created for terms in the ontology
        sourceFile - the path for the file from which to import the ontology, if not from the URI
        ontology - the existing FortImpl representing the ontology, if we are to update an already-imported ontology
        quotedIsa - the collection of which newly created terms should be quoted instances. If null, Cyc will create one.
        cyclist - the cyclist to attribute the new terms and assertions to
        Returns:
        the FortImpl representing the imported ontology
        Throws:
        CycConnectionException - if a communications error occurs
        CycApiException - if the Cyc server returns an error
